==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{qualifier|obsolete}} {{l|en|acceptaunce}}

===Etymology===
First attested in 1574. From {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|acceptance}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|accepter||accept}}. Equivalent to {{suffix|accept|ance|nocat=1|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ək.ˈsɛp.təns/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|En-us-acceptance.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of [[accepting]]; a receiving of something offered, with approbation, satisfaction, or [[acquiescence]]; especially, favorable [[reception]]; [[approval]]
#: ''the '''acceptance''' of a gift, office, doctrine, etc.''
#* ''Isaiah 60:7'':
#*: They shall come up with '''acceptance''' on mine altar.
# Belief in something; [[agreement]]; [[assent]].
# State of being [[accept]]ed.
#* Shakespeare: ''Rape of Lucrece'':
#*: Makes it assured of '''acceptance'''.
# {{label|en|business|finance}} An assent and [[engagement]] by the person on whom a [[bill of exchange]] is drawn, to pay it when due according to the terms of the [[acceptance]].
# {{label|en|business|finance}} The [[bill of exchange]] itself when accepted.
# An [[agreeing]] to terms or [[proposals]] by which a bargain is [[concluded]] and the parties are bound; the reception or taking of a thing [[bought]] as that for which it was bought, or as that agreed to be delivered, or the taking possession as owner.
# {{label|en|legal}} An agreeing to the action of another, by some act which binds the person in law.
# {{label|en|US|government}} The act of an authorized representative of the Government by which the Government assents to ownership by it of existing and identified supplies, or approves specific services rendered, as partial or complete performance of a contract.
# The usual or accepted meaning of a word or expression.
# {{label|en|Australia|New Zealand|pluralonly}} A list of [[horse]]s accepted as [[starter]]s in a [[race]].

====Usage notes====
* {{sense|legal|An agreeing to the action of another, by some act which binds the person in law}} In modern law, proposal and '''acceptance''' are the constituent elements into which all contracts are resolved.

